text: Agree that the example chosen was really bad and writing through it was painful. I really hoped mj would be able to clarify better how to handle this strange case. Overall though, i really liked the exercise and thought there were​ good points throughout; retro-style, like you said, but with the added structure so you might know more readily what to change in the future. Where, in our current process, I don't think those outcomes are so obvious.
